default3.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnergydefault3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe strongly support the zero carbon 2016/2019 policies, and we agree that fabric energy efficiency standards are the domain of national standards and so we broadly support the approach outlined in the consultation document. 
default&#xa0;
default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, t
defaulthere is always going to be an interplay between building regulations and planning on energy issues. Building regulations should take care of fabric efficiency, onsite carbon compliance and Allowable Solutions, but plann
defaulters
default should have input into the renewable energy strategy for the development. We agree that the rather blunt 'Merton rule' approach, whereby a percentage of renewable energy is required, is 
defaultusually not the right approach. However, we agree that where viable, 
defaultL
defaultP
defaultAs should be able to require developers to link up to
default low carbon or
default 
defaultrenewable energy 
defaultschemes where they exist,
default or will exist in the future,
default as part of a borough wide plan for low carbon and renewable energy.
default&#xa0;
default3.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthere are 
defaultenergy related issues
default 
defaultwhich are currently in the CSH, but not 
defaultin the proposed new standards. These include:
default&#xa0;
default3.3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDrying space – this is a key element to provide healthy internal environments in the context of increasing air tightness. The Code requires clothes drying provision within the bathroom and the space be mechanically ventilated 
defaultwith a humidistat control. This issue should be taken account of in 
defaultBuilding Regulations Part F.
default&#xa0;
default3.3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnergy efficient white goods
default. Our 
defaultmembers’ 
defaultexperience is that the Code does 
defaultimpact on 
defaultthe 
defaultefficiency of the 
defaultwhite goods which are installed in dwellings.
default Low efficiency white goods are, unfortunately, still available
default.
