default6.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe HSR process was 
defaultinadequate when it came to considering materi
defaultals. 
defaultA materials expert group should be set up as soon as possible to advise on this matter and where best in the regulations these issues should be addressed.
default&#xa0;
defaultOther issuesdefault&#xa0;default7.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEcologydefault7.1default&#xa0; 
defaultIt is not clear from the consultation document what the proposals are for dealing with the ecology credits from the CSH. Indeed, the issue of ecology is not mentioned at all. We think the CSH has spurred developers into thinking more about ecology at the design stage, and would not want to see its importance downgraded with the demise of the CSH. We agree that ecology is a planning issue, and we think the government should make clear that in the absence of the CSH, all LPAs should have clear policies for improving the ecological value of land through development, as part of their local plan
default.
